I know it's a little late, but same-sex marriage is legal in Florida.

37 states it's legal and 72% of the usa lives in states where same sex marriage is legal.

The fifth and eighth circuit appeals courts are currently hearing cases.

The only states where it's still illegal and the circuit courts haven't decided to hear the cases are Missouri, Kentucky, Ohio, Tennesse, Alabama, Georgia.  Those last six states are probably going to be hard cause they're part of the sixth and eleventh circuit.  The sixth circuit is vehemntly opposed to hearing any cases.  The eleventh circuit is probably going to be the first cause the circuit court refused to hear the case on Florida.

Basically my money is on 2016 the *ONLY* place where gay marriage is still illegal is in the sixth circuit.
*Starts laughing at that Texas and the south is probably going to legalize same-sex marriage before Ohio or Missouri.
